  <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">How to use the <abbr>PSD</abbr></h1>
  <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
    An introduction to using the Product Safety Database (<abbr>PSD</abbr>) online digital service.
  </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
  <div class="govuk-!-margin-bottom-8 govuk-!-padding-top-5 govuk-!-padding-right-4 govuk-!-padding-bottom-1 govuk-!-padding-left-5 opss-blue-border-all">
    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">
      In early 2023 - How notifications work and are created was changed
    </h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Previously, when a notification was created, basic information describing a product was automatically required and formed part of the <abbr>PSD</abbr> notification. Instead, notifications now include - or link to - product records. It is the product record which now records the basic information about the product.
    </p>
    <div class="govuk-inset-text">
      <p class="govuk-body">
        A notification and a product are now two separate <br>entities within the <abbr>PSD</abbr>.
      </p>
    </div>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Notifications record information about supply chains, evidence, and corrective actions. A product record describes the product and is included within a notification.
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      The same product record can now be included within many different notifications.
    </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

