    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">
      <span class="govuk-!-font-weight-regular">Guidance</span> <br>
      Notification of unsafe and noncompliant products
    </h2>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      For guidance and information on how market surveillance authorities should notify products, which pose a risk to the health and safety of consumers and / or are noncompliant, visit:
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/notification-of-unsafe-and-noncompliant-products" class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">Notification of unsafe and noncompliant products (opens in a new tab)</a>
    </p>
    <img loading="lazy" src="<%= image_path "help/about/guideance-document-icon.png" %>" class="opss-border-all" alt="Guideance document icon">

    <hr class="govuk-section-break-m">
    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">When to use the <abbr>PSD</abbr></h2>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">You can use the <abbr>PSD</abbr> to:</p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-list--spaced govuk-body-s">
      <li>
        notify products posing a risk to the health and safety of consumers and/or products which are noncompliant by creating <abbr>PSD</abbr> notifications
      </li>
      <li>
        assign notifications to, and receive referrals from, Local Authorities or organisations and track the notification progress
      </li>
      <li>
        search for products or businesses already notified in the <abbr>PSD</abbr>
      </li>
      <li>
        search for products and view all the notifications which have been created about the product
      </li>
      <li>
        take corrective action to restrict the availability of a product on the market
      </li>
      <li>
        add more evidence to notifications as it is gathered
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="govuk-body-s">
      You should add the <abbr>OPSS</abbr> Incident Management Team (<abbr>IMT</abbr>) to a notification if the product is a high or serious risk, or the product has been recalled.
    </p>
  </aside>
